    <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
      <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
      <p>Dorothy Lobrano (Mrs. Raymond C.) Guth is the daughter of long-time
        (1938-1956) New Yorker fiction editor, Gus Lobrano (Class of 1924) and the
        goddaughter of E. B. White. In 1976, she collected and edited an edition of the
        Letters of E. B. White.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
      <p>Letters, manuscripts, galley proofs, and other materials relating to
        the publication of the Letters of E. B. White. Includes numerous letters from
        White to Guth.</p>
    </scopecontent>
